Phrase: -In the beginning I was just a bandit.
I am Anna. A servant who was a former bandit. Before I was captured and employed in this castle, I used to sneak into rich people's houses and castles to steal bread and wheat.
I never stole gold and jewelry. That night, too, my aim was the castle pantry.
I made the mistake of trying to get at the good loot in the chaos of the war. I tried to steal cakes as well as bread. On the night I robbed the castle, there was a birthday party at the castle.
The daughter of the lord of this castle. Her 15th birthday. A beautiful girl my age.
She was performing a song in front of her followers when she smiled at me, the intruder, and said,
-Would you like to join us?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: This is a very large prison compared to the ones I've seen. Is the owner of the voice locked up in this prison?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Is there anyone here? If so, please answer me.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: It's about time you should gave me some hints...
Hello, there.
I'm glad you've came. I admire your courage to go alone to this prison under these circumstances.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: This is only my duty. I did what was necessary.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I'm sure you're the one who called us earlier. I can't see you, but you have the same tone of voice.
I can see you from here. The nice maid with the long ears.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I am Victoria. I serve Lady Paddington, fifth daughter of the House of Elrond.

Name: Anna
Phrase: My name is Anna. I am a maid here at this castle.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Well now, we are both maids serving our mistresses. You seem somewhat like me.

Name: Anna
Phrase: I am not a great maid like you. I am a maid now, but soon I will be sent to the battlefield.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Some maids are like that. I am a good example.

Name: Anna
Phrase: You too?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Yes. I am also a knight. I have come in to investigate your castle on a mission. Please forgive me for being a little rude towards you earlier, as lives were at stake.

Name: Anna
Phrase: No, you did well to break through that door. I feel reassured knowing that you're a knight.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Is something troubling you?

Name: Anna
Phrase: This castle is cursed by a certain someone. It is cursed to rain forever and ever.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Let's make this a quick story. We're investigating this endless rain. Do you know the cause of the curse?

Name: Anna
Phrase: Yes, I do. There is a person who is casting the curse. I know that person very well.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Where is that person now?

Name: Anna
Phrase: She is here in the castle. She is my mistress.

Name: Anna
Phrase: My Lady is under grounded in a small room in a separate tower. My Lady is unaware that she has casted a curse on herself. She needs to stop praying for rain as soon as possible...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Praying for rain...

Name: Anna
Phrase: We don't have much time. I must save my mistress. Demons are after the young mistress. The curse must be lifted before the demons take her, or the country will sink to the bottom of the lake.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Come, Victoria, release me quickly. You can break the lock to this prison. I need you to destroy it with your weapon.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Leave it to me. As long as there's no strange magic involved, a key to a prison cell is just a matter of...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Are you sure, Victoria? From now on, you are a member of the SSS. Sometimes you have to think with your head in order to protect Conductor. Sometimes the 'Lucy Squad' way doesn't work.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: I know I know. You're not very good at thinking with your head. I know you very well, Victoria, you've always solved everything with power, and sometimes you make things worse.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: But if you absolutely cannot fail, do stop and think about it. If you still can't think of anything, then you can do whatever you want, Victoria!

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Don't worry, you're not alone Victoria. I'm just as bad as you at thinking!

Name: Anna
Phrase: Victoria, what's wrong?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: My sincerest apologies. My Lady has told me to stop and think when it's important. 'When it's critical, stop and think'.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Before I release you, I would like to know why you are locked up in this dungeon. If you are working as a chambermaid and is ready to go to war, why are you locked in a dungeon like this?

Name: Anna
Phrase: That's because...

Name: Anna
Phrase: Because this is where I belong.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: So you are a sinner. You have been lying to me.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Indeed I am a sinner. But I have not lied to you.

Name: Anna
Phrase: I am a maid, but I was once a mere bandit. I was pardoned by my young mistress and received the status of maid of honor. Because of my combat training and experience. I was hired on condition that I would go into battle as a soldier in this castle.

Name: Anna
Phrase: I am only kept alive to do my job as a mercenary. I was thrown back into the dungeon where I used to be for a minor misbehaviour.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Well, that's unfortunate. If I worked under the same conditions, I would have never get out of the dungeons.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Why were you punished? I don't think one should be locked up in a prison like this simply for breaking a cup or a glass.

Name: Anna
Phrase: They found out that I was having a 'secret tea party' with my young Lady.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: What's a 'secret tea party'?

Name: Anna
Phrase: It's a code used to describe a meeting between two people.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Ever since mistress's fifteenth birthday, my Lady will catch a fever as soon as she is exposed to rain and wind. Since then I have been forbidden to enter my Lady's room.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: So that's why you started meeting her in secret. And is this dungeon is your 'secret place'?

Name: Anna
Phrase: Please. Please believe me. I am the only one who has access to my Lady's room. Without the secret duplicate key, I cannot save my mistress.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I understand. I believe you.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Thank you. Thank you so much!

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I'll destroy the grating. If it's only this thick, I can break it with one blow.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Be careful. There's a drain under your feet, so don't fall in.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I understand. Miss Anna, please stay as far away from the grate as possible.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Just call me Anna, Victoria.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Alright, Anna, here I go.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: ...It is open.

Name: Anna
Phrase: Thank you Victoria! I will never forget what you did for me!

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Please wait. Please return the lights as you promised...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Ah, how very kind of you...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Victoria! Are you okay!?

Name: Putra
Phrase: It looks like you were talking to someone, was there anyone there?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Yes, someone called Anna, who works here at the castle.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Where did that person go to ...?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Perhaps she went to the other tower to help the young mistress.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: So you have found out something.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Yes, Anna's purpose is the same as ours. She went to her mistress to clear this rain.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Saving her mistress will clear the rain. That's why she ran out in such a hurry.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Victoria, can I ask you something? About this... Anna person.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Verily. I will tell you.
